        "harmful_notes": "Amorphous silicon dioxide (SiO2) used as anti-caking agent in tablets/capsules at <2% w/w. FDA GRAS (21 CFR 172.480, max 2% of food weight). EFSA 2018 re-evaluation could not confirm safety due to insufficient nanoparticle characterization data — this was a data gap, not a finding of harm. Amorphous SiO2 is poorly absorbed from the GI tract. Nanoparticle concerns are based on in vitro studies at concentrations far exceeding dietary exposure.",
